< Review>
Chicken 65 biryani:
Ohhh my gosh. This is good! The chicken is thoroughly coated and soaked with herbs and spices that there's a red color even inside. It's not crispy but there is a very very thin coat of breading. I wish there were more. The yogurt sauce is refreshing. The gravy is pretty tasty too and adds more depth to your bite; like a concentrated version of the biryani flavor but with maybe some chicken stock? I'm not sure.</Review>

<username>Justine Langston<//username><user>116251146844879855772</user><Text>It looked like these folks were having a bit of a rough night when I went to pick up my order-- they seemed understaffed.  However, my order was ready on time, and once I brought it home turned out to be perfect and delicious! Best Mysore Masala Dosa I've had in a long time (which I was suspicious of ordering to-go but was just fine if not super crispy), great dhal fry and I was very happy with the eggplant and tamarind dish which I'd never tried before.  I spent quite a bit of time in southern Indian, and though I was not familiar with chettinad cuisine specifically, this definitely hits the spot for other classics.  I will certainly return to try a few more dishes, I hope they stay busy so that they can perhaps hire a bit more help.< /Text>< Rate>

<Review>3.5 stars. The food is good! I'm giving this 3.5 stars due to the service - the whole place was empty but they wanted to seat us one table away from another occupied table (we promptly moved several tables away) and the service was a little slow even though the in-dining was not too busy.

We ordered the tomato soup and a ghee podi dosai to share. The tomato soup was soothing to my soul.  I've gotten away from having it as frequently since I moved to the United States so this was a good change and brought back memories from home. Good garlic kick with a hint of spicy. Liked it.

The ghee podi dosai was good too. Pretty big for one person, the chutney inside the dosai was spicy as expected. The chutneys accompanying the dosai were good. The sambar was ok.

We don't live in the area but if we come back, will consider take out.<//Review>< Pics>

The quantity of the thali is too much for one person though.<//Text><date>1578261785038</date><GmapID>0x80dcdb6c7d30e34d:0x12b831338058047a</GmapID><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPbOYYU_5-cOpoBDNonACD2t6qkDs3AIywyAfth=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMOZH-GlcXDqIq2BNBiTmbC02xsQ5KPwmyo1gp-=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipM5pj03DZISYj7_iUNl2CqpL30PQP7fTSBI_R1p=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /Pictures>< UserId.>
113395092295102909293</UserId.>
< username>
Sharad Manasali</username>
<rating>4<//rating></record></dataset><record>
< Text>
When in OC and craving for Chettinad food, then Anjappar is the place to head to without a second thought. Until last year, the only Anjappar in the vicinity was about an hour's drive away in Artesia, so visiting the place occurred once-in-a-blue-moon. But ever since they opened a branch in nearby Tustin, our visits to the nearest Anjappar have become way more frequent - be it to dine in or to pickup some spicy grub!

The ambience is lively and the interior decor is very pretty, especially the mural of a peacock. There are quite a few tables that are decently spread out, but you might have to wait for a while to get seated if you show up during their peak hours. That said, their service is prompt and the staff are quite cheerful and friendly.

Though it's hard to go wrong with the food selection here, there are quite a few options to choose from and it's easy to get lost in the menu. When visiting with friends during lunch hours, we usually order their Virundhu thaali (translates to feast) which has a plethora of food items that are more than enough for two people with a good apetite! Recently we went for dinner and sought help in deciding which a la carte items to order. Nithya kindly recommended the Egg Curry to go with the Idiyappam combo and Appam combo, and had us sold on the Vavval Varuval (Pomfret Fish Fry), and each of these items was delish! We ordered the Mutton Biryani with Seeraga Samba Rice and Nattukkoli Masala (Country Chicken Curry) to go, and enjoyed the food over the next couple of days (amazing how already tasty food becomes yummier and spicier after a day or two!). What better way to top off a hearty and spicy meal than the Desi way of having a Sweet Paan (an assortment of ingredients wrapped together in a Betel leaf)! Burp!

Never have I walked away from Anjappar feeling disappointed in any way. I sure hope they keep up the great work!< /Text>

<Rate>2</Rate>< Text>
The food for the most part was good.   Avoid the garlic nan as it was dry and seemed to be made with poor quality flour.  Also the rice was dry and was breaking into pieces.  The service was very very poor.  Neither the manager nor the staff were trained.  We waited a long time for our order to be taken.  Then my wife's food came out, my food came out a full 10 minutes after my wife's and my daughter's food came out about 5 minutes after mine and only after we inquired about her dinner.  A kitchen staff member even came out with my daughter's dinner and took it to the wrong table and then back to the kitchen before finally bringing it to our table.  Also they gave my wife a Samber portion in a chutney bowl so there was not enough.  Even the waiters don't know how to pour water as they reach across guest when they could walk around the table. Also the water glasses are half the size they should be.

The manager also mumbles so you can't understand what he is saying and when he brought the bill to me (no comps even after we complained about the poor service and timing of our food), he hovered over me while I was reviewing the bill in writing in the tip.  The manager has no clue what he is doing and didn't know how to react to a proper service complaint.

This place either needs to train all its front of the kitchen employees or need to hire new people.

The food is not good enough to overcome the poor service.</Text>

<userid>110239633349088513540</userid><name>Pradeep Mohanannair< /name><Date>1580011788091</Date>< rate>

<Review>One of the best Indian restaurants around this area, when you don‚Äôt have to drive to Pioneer blvd. This place is primarily a South Indian place, but they do have north Indian cuisine choices too.
Located in convenient location in Newport Ave, but parking here might get tight. Always crowded, so be prepared to wait for seating.
Friendly and fairly quick service. Neatly maintained and hygienic place, pretty safe for kids too.
We ordered following

Appetizer:
Chicken Lollipop, crispy and well cooked to perfection, not too spicy.
Chicken 65: Soft and well cooked, very flavorful.
Egg Bonda, was just ok.

Main Dish:
Chettinad Chicken: Very flavorful with lot of pepper, best part of the order is the requested spicy level is met excited.
Nattukkoli Masala: Very authentic tmailnadu recipe, perfectly churned in grinded masala, very garlic flavor induced.
We ordered Parotta, Chappathi, Naan, Aappam to go with that.
We also ordered Mutton Biriyani, no complaints. Very good flavors and rice cooked to perfection.

Beverage:
Jigarthanda, a sought-after milk-based drink, very famous in city of Madurai and across Tamilnadu. A must try, very rich drink. But please share, its too much to drink for just one.
Mango Lassi, just as expected.
Overall, very comfort, very delicious food for affordable price.
Next time, I want to try non-veg thaali.< /Review>< Pics>
None</Pics>

<Resp>None<//Resp>< text>
Treated a non-Indian friend to lunch here (I am Indian); we ordered chicken 65 appetizer, masala dosa tiffin, poori with vegetable kuruma, and mushroom biryani and asked for everything to be very spicy. We planned to take home leftovers to share with our husbands later.

The chicken 65 was very tasty, and oddly enough, the most spicy, even though it was only a little spicy. The dosa was also good though the potato masala wasn't spicy. But the poori which took forever to arrive was hard, and the vegetable kuruma was so mild it tasted bland to me. These arrived after we'd finished eating so I took it home. The mushroom biryani was good but not spicy enough. I asked for pickle to spice things up,  and was told there was no pickle, and was brought a little dish of sriracha instead! It was not inexpensive so I was disappointed. So many other reviewers have described the food as too spicy so I'm wondering if I went on an off day or perhaps the consistency of food varies from day to day.<//text>

<rating>4< /rating>< review>
Food is closest to the real thing, service is excellent. The richness of the spices come out in a light aroma but tastes so deep you can savor home cooking in every dish. A friend ordered things for my group so I didn't get to know the names of the plates but the Mutton Dum Biryani and Crab Roast Masala stand out. The Crab Roast might be too spicy for some but if you spicy this is a must. Enjoy!</review>

<Name>T Gupta</Name><Time>1558480058270<//Time>< rate>
5< /rate>
< Review>
Very Friendly and Cooperative Staff with very good service rarely seen in India restaurants.

We went on Mother's day and were told of wait time of 1 hour but got a text in 25 minutes that we missed. came back to inquire after 50 minutes but without any expression that we missed the text, they accommodated us within 5 minutes.

On Mother's day, service and quality can go wrong at any restaurant and I had already resigned to this fact but surprisingly neither quality, nor the service was sub-par. Though we were told before ordering that certain dishes were not available; which is good because most of time, when you ask for a dish, then you are told of non-availability.

Imtiyaz and Shiva were excellent and the server who took and planned our order was also very nice (the same server moved from Natraj to Inchin to this place)

Food could be a bit spicy for a person who does not eat any spice were overall very balanced spices and a variety of taste to explore.< /Review>

<text>If you are looking for the best south India non-vegetarian food, then Anjappar is a must visit! We really loved the mutton bone soup, chicken fry, curries (chicken, mutton, fish). Vegetarians who love South Indian tiffin items should try out some of their authentic south Indian stuff (I'm not referring to idli and dosa!). <rating>5<//rating><Review>Excellent service and delicious preparation. Chettinad is a region in Tamilnadu, India. Chettinad food is generally extremely spicy, and though I love it, my kids find traditional Chettinad food difficult to eat. At this place, the chillies have been toned down a little, but without compromising the flavor. Definitely recommend the Kashmiri Pulav (which is sweet) paired with a spicy mutton or fish dish.

<text>A couple of girls at my work get their nails done here, and they're always immaculate, so I made an appointment one Wednesday afternoon...
I was coming from a weird job, and already smack dab in the middle of a looooonnng-ass day when I arrived.  I was looking pretty dishevelled; man, these ladies looked at me like they had just seen me climb out of a dumpster and walk in their door!
I forget the name of the girl who did my acrylic full set, she was young and pretty. I really do feel like my appearance that day influenced how I was treated. The girl is skilled at shaping nails just so, even when rushing through the job (something they do everywhere) but there was this rudeness and roughness in the way she spoke to me and handled my precious little paws. At the tail end of buffing & shaping , she got up, went and got a phone, and placed a personal call, which she remained on - shooting the breeze, gossiping, and making plans for later(in English!), through the remainder of my appointment.
The nails still came out beautifully. For various reasons, I had to wait a whole month to get a fill, but I had absolutely zero lifting or breaking in that time!
A full acrylic set with plain polish set me back forty dollars - $15-20 more than I'm used to paying. I left a decent tip ($5) even though the service was really bull. What can I say? I work for tips, so I can't bear to skip out on tips. Some kinda karma deal.
The nails came out delicate, perfectly shaped, lasting. I would definitely go back here based on the quality of work, despite her attitude.  The only reason I probably will not return is the price. There are plenty of spots closer to home that do an acceptable job and charge way less. I am a little curious though, about if I go back in looking rested and put together, if they'd treat me any more respectfully...< /text></record>

<Time>1616465049946</Time><rating>5<//rating><text>I was referred to Dr. Winter from my wife after I had sustained a chipped tooth. I was told that she was great with cosmetic dentistry and that her and her entire office staff was extremely friendly. My experience was just that and more! Upon entering, Alicia and Deb at the front desk were super friendly and helpful which is huge to me since dentist visits are not generally my most exciting appointments. I was then escorted back by Kat whom I believe was the dental assistant and she too was very friendly and gave me a tour of the office and introduced me to most of the other staff members that we passed by. Once taken to my chair, Kat helped answer all of my questions and helped me understand what we were doing that day and what to expect. When Dr. Winter came in, she was also very nice and friendly like no other dentist I've gone to. As her and Kat were doing their work, they checked in with me periodically to make sure I was doing fine and I don't think I had ever felt so relaxed during dental work! I almost felt as though I could have dozed off in a good, relaxing way. I was impressed at how well my tooth looked after the appointment and started discussing other dental plans I had considered. After the initial visit, I scheduled my next visit and plan to be a long time patient from here forward! We bought my sister a fire place insert model EP24789 fireplace at Christmas.  This insert is a fire hazard.  We tested it for a few minutes to make sure it worked. It came with a 15 amp plug.  The booklet it came with also stated it was a 15 amp plug and Costway's website also states it.  She used it on low setting for short intervals. During a cold snap she put it on the high setting for 15 minutes to get the chill out of the room. As she went to unplug it, the plug was hot. She had an electrician look at the outlet, which was fine and that the fireplace and/or plug must be defected.  After contacting Costway, we were told she needed a 20 amp outlet.  We wrote them back asking why does the fireplace have a 15 amp plug, and the booklet and website state 15 amp?  They said they would take it back and refund us only if we had the original box and wrapping.  This was a Christmas gift, it had been over 2 months, we did not save the box or original wrapping.  They came back and said we could keep it and they would only refund us $50.  This is wrong on so many levels.  The fire place insert is a fire hazard, and could have caused a fire and worst scenario, death.  They should take the fire place insert back without original box and refund us the full amount.   I would never buy anything from this company again.  I rate the product 0 stars and their customer services 0 stars.  So disappointed in a company not taking responsibility for their product.< /Review>

< Text>
I recently received this kitchen island from Costway, and it is perfect for my small kitchen. I really needed something that would provide me with not only a nice prep and beverage space, but also some extra storage. This kitchen island boasts two cabinets, one larger and one smaller, as well as two drawers. The shelves in the cabinets are easily adjustable to fit your needs. The cabinets open easy, but are also secure with a magnet closure. The drawers glide open like a dream, but have a stopper, as to not accidentally pull the entire drawer out. If you have kids, like I do, you know how important it is for those drawer stoppers to work. The island also features a knife block on the end. One of my favorite features of this island is that it has wheels to easily move it. This is so convenient for cleaning underneath and behind it. The handle, that is on the end, also helps you easily move the island, but also can be used as a kitchen towel or paper towel rack. Overall, this kitchen island is aesthetically pleasing. The materials used to make this are pretty sturdy. One thing I‚Äôd like to touch on is the directions and packaging. I can‚Äôt tell you how many times I‚Äôve bought things elsewhere where the directions are terrible, and all the hardware is thrown into one bag. That is not the case at all with this! The directions were very clear and easy to follow, and all hardware was bagged separately and labeled. This made putting the island together so much quicker. If you are on the fence about an item, don‚Äôt hesitate! You won‚Äôt be able to find the same quality for the price. Plus, don‚Äôt forget you get fast and free shipping. Do yourself a favor and order; you won‚Äôt be sorry!

I was also in the market for a bunk bed for my kids room. I needed one with solid construction, so it would grow with them but also wanted one that was not going to break the bank. This bunk bed definitely fit the bill. After ordering, it took about 2-3 days to arrive. Everything was well packed and protected. It took my husband about an hour to assemble. The process of putting it together goes so much faster, as they have everything clearly labeled and hardware is sorted out into individual bags. One thing my husband really liked was that the mattress slats were tethered together for each bunk. This takes the guess work out of how many to use or how far to space them. The wood is pretty solid and not the really cheap stuff. The bed is very stable, and I like that it is not squeaky if my kids move, like some other beds. The bottom bunk sits higher off the ground and provides ample room to store stuff under the bed, if you would like. Another plus is that this bed is versatile and can be separated into 2 twin size beds, if we choose to do so. Overall, my kids are absolutely thrilled with their bunk bed, and so am I.</Text>

I have purchased a compact folding treadmill (LOVE IT) Adjustable folding ladder (perfect for my cabin) Mini Circular saw (wish I had this the last 6 months). I am very happy with all my purchases.

Absolutely loving my Costway Modern Tufted Accent Chair:  Mid Century Modern Upholstered Accent Chair, w/ Rubber Wood Legs, Button Tufted Armchair, Linen Fabric Single Sofa for Living Room, Bedroom, Office (costway.com)
My wife really enjoys curling up in this chair with a good book. The material is comfortable yet durable enough for our dog Piper to get in a nap on the chair (until she is caught üòä and we say get down) I personally like the mix of comfort design this chair offers, the bottom cushion is firm yet comfortable for long sitting times while the back support has a soft pillow design which I find very relaxing.
I really like that the back support can be easily removed with a firm pull, this lightens the load and makes it easier to move the chair from room to room and through tight spaces. The construction of this chair is very solid. I found it extremely easy to put together. The most amount of time assembling this chair is fastening the legs to the base. Each leg on the chair has 4 bolts that insure a secure fix to the chair base. Like any product take your time and read the assembly instructions.
Absolutely loving this Costway Modern Tufted Accent Chair! So pleased with the purchase!</review>

<name>Tim Hobbs< /name><Time>1602116571027< /Time>< rating>
4<//rating>
<review>The chair comes disassembled and took about 30-45 minutes to put together at a leisurely pace. The instructions could be a bit easier to understand but if you have assembled any furniture it is pretty much the same thing. The hardware comes in a nice little package so you don't have to dig through the box to find parts.

I was impressed by the overall quality. The feel is nice. My daughter thought it was really cool :)

The chair is comfortable and the adjustment options are nice: up/down, arms up/down and swivel in/out, and the recline feature is cool though not sure how practical. To be honest when I tested it out it went so far back I thought I was going to fall backwards. I don't even think I reclined it all the way! The one thing that would be nice is if the arm width could be adjusted - right now it would require adjusting the screws.

I work full time from home so I am pretty decently versed in chair prices and for any decent chair you would pay the same or more, so it seems like a decent price and value. I know that many similar "gamer" chairs can run up to 5x more.</review><pictures>None< /pictures>< resp>

< review>
So I started out buying a vibrating pc chair from costway unknowingly via walmart; when it got all messed up and my chair was returned to costway. When I contacted walmart of course they didn‚Äôt care they didn‚Äôt even respond. I searched and found out who the seller was and emailed them. Costway expedited shipping/provided an excellent discount and was very kind, so when the chair didn‚Äôt work I figured they would not care. Total opposite they shipped me another free of charge! What a great company and they have earned a customer for life!!

106193739314524460525<//user_id>
<username>Stefan Gombas< /username>< Time>
1600121129390< /Time>
<rating>2</rating><Text>I purchased an office/gaming desk off of Amazon. First thing to note is that this product is claimed to be made by Tangkula, which is actually a company based out of California by the name of Costway. The desk arrived in two separate packages when it could easily been one, which leads me to believe the desktop and support system come from different locations...little odd but whatever.

Both boxes arrive and I start assembly. There are a few surface imperfections in faux wood grain as shown in picture. ‚ÄúWooden‚Äù pieces and the black mid section are adjoined by small wooden pegs and reinforced by metal runners. Seems like the hole thing should more securely fastened together. Hexagonal bolts fasten everything together, but poor quality control made it rough to assemble as receiving holes were not properly reamed out.

Next my issue dealing with customer support arises. I found that my packages did not include 2 of the parts necessary to complete construction. I contacted the actual company Costway through their email found on their website and through here on Amazon. Only way to contact them is through email, and it took a long time to finally get a hold of someone. We spoke via email over the course of several days because they only answer in the middle of the night (EASTERN US TIMEZONE). First they told me they didn‚Äôt have those parts in stock and it would be 25-30 days until they got more in from China. They offered to compensate me $30 for my wait, but I said no and that if the parts were not there within a week I‚Äôd like a refund. So ‚Äúsurprise‚Äù they decided to send me an entire half of the order with all the hardware and legs (could of just taken those missing parts out of the box). Customer service was not rude, but hard to reach and odd to deal with.

After I got my replacement parts I finish putting the desk together as detailed. The remaining bolts holes could also used reamed as I said before. Washers would also help prevent any over torque since they need to be securely tightened to prevent any wobbling. As shown in the picture there is a small 1/8‚Äù gap on one side between faux wood and black mid section due to poor quality control.

Overall the desk looks nice minus the surface imperfections and panel gaps. The adjustable legs are nice since I live in an older home with uneven floors. That does not excuse the missing parts, hard to reach customer service, and poor quality control. I would not make another purchase from Tangkula AKA Costway AKA Any Other Brand They Use.

PROS:
Simple steps for constructions
Looks nice
Adjustable feet

CONS:
Poor quality control
Missing parts upon arrival

< Text>
I ordered this ice make from Amazon for our soon to be new kitchen in November 2019. It was delivered and sat in the box and till March when were finally able to install it under our sink. We opened the box, there was no damage to it, everything was in tact and packed perfectly, and then we plugged it in, connected the water supply and turned it on.
As soon as we turned it on the tub started to fill with water. It was able to make ice but the ice fell in the tub of water. I called Costway and was instructed to email their customer service. I couldn't speak to anyone all concerns were to be emailed. I did that and their response times is 24-48hrs. After several emails back and forth sending videos and pics they said the machine was missing the plug and they would send me one. They sent me the plug for the unit 3 different times because i never received it. I finally received it in July, installed the plug, turned the machine on and no leaks! Woo hoo, now I can finally use my ice maker! NOT!!!! Although the machine didn't leak it produced very soft ice and couldn't keep it frozen. All the ice that was made would fall in the tub and melt, until the tub was finally filled with water and half melted ice. It got to the point where the machine would produce ice and it would fall in the tub of water and the water would overflow onto the floor so we had to turn it off. I've been trying to call Costway for the past week. No ring, just busy signal. I also emailed them waiting for a response, which i think is going to come from China which isn't all that great cause they are not very clear with their info. not to mention their instruction manual sucks!  Worst thing ever! The machine also produces a lot of noise to have in a kitchen.
I hate this thing, most of all I hate the customer service offered by Costway. I have a feeling they are going to ask me to get the machine checked or something on my dime, or blame it on me who knows. I'm also going to email Amazon. We are on a budget. I saved up money for this unit. I choose it because it had mostly good reviews. Apparently I got the lemon. All I want is a machine that works. is that too much to ask. Don't buy this unit!!< /Text>

< Text>
I purchased a GO PLUS Magnetic Exercise Bike Stationary Belt Drive Indoor Cycling Bike. Upon receiving I noticed there was an incomplete part discovered during assembly. I contacted Costway via email and twitter with picture and information. They responded and sent me the complete molded part. It took some time to recieve the part as that was explained in the initial correspondence and it was close to the time Costway customer service said it would take. While I waited for part I was able to make bike functional in the meantime. But needless to say the bike is solid now with the complete molded part. I give the review 4 stars for that reason. It's winter/snow where I live right now and I have no concern about the elements outside because I have a workout room set up and now this indoor bike to complete my 24 hour fitness area in my place. I'm 56 and I bike often in the summer outside. It's an important part of my complete workouts and have spent more than a few winters suffering by not having that option indoors. I do not have that concern anymore. Anytime day or night it can be GO TIME on this bike. The heavy 30 lb flywheel is just right. The belt drive is whisper quiet. And the magnets. Oh man.... I just rotated the adjustable knob in a full 360¬∞to move the magnets closer to the flywheel. The new resistance level is kickin my butt so my numbers for speed and distance are lower of course on the LCD monitor that also observes time, calorie and heart rate. But that's what great workouts are about. Time to climb that mountain all over again. I can't begin to describe how great the workouts are with this spinner bike. It's full-on intense and worth every minute. Just what I was hoping for when I bought it. I wish the LCD monitor would show miles instead of kilometers but it's not difficult to calculate your kilometers to miles, kph to mph, etc. That would be the other reason I gave 4 stars for this review. In closing. Thanks Costway for a great spinner/indoor bike. I bought this on Cyber Monday and Costway provided a hard to turn down discount that also  included free shipping that swayed me from buying another bike from a different company. This Go Plus bike may not be a famous brand name. But at this point it is my experience and opinion that I would put it right up there with any spinner bike that has comparable specs/features.< /Text>
